website_summaries.verdict: The true wireless JLab JBuds Air Executive earphones cost just $69 but offer merely average audio quality.
cons: Bass-boosted, sculpted audio throws off balance

website_summaries.verdict: The JBuds do offer excellent battery life, perform very well on phone calls, and video syncing is solid. It’s a shame then that the audio performance just doesn’t impress. The three EQs somehow manage to strip mixes of those vital ingredients that make them truly come alive. You can enjoy listening to music and spoken work audio on the JBuds, of that there’s no doubt, but when you’re spending this much you expect just a bit more sparkle than these earbuds deliver. There are better options out there around this price.

customer_reviews.title: Disappointing quality
customer_reviews.text: Sound is alright at best but unfortunately I can't comment much more as the right earbud stopped working after one day. Not a connection issue, the speaker just died.
customer_reviews.author: Ryen Stork

customer_reviews.title: Disappointing
customer_reviews.text: Order received today and charging port is damaged so right earphones won't charge. Little disappointed as I've now got to return and wait for a refund.
customer_reviews.author: Mark C.

customer_reviews.title: Unable to rate as returned to amazon
customer_reviews.text: Didn’t even get a chance to rate the sound quality as they were too big to fit into my sons ear
customer_reviews.author: Gary Mc

customer_reviews.title: Big talk but generally underwhelming.
customer_reviews.text: Sound quality is ok. Microphone and call quality are not that good, noise cancellation doesn't really work. Is probably worse that £30 alternatives.
customer_reviews.author: Moha

customer_reviews.title: Total crap.
customer_reviews.text: Horrible sound and the "Be aware" feature is crap. I bought the Anker Soundcore's instead for less and they're amazing.
customer_reviews.author: Joseph Tracy

customer_reviews.title: Broken in less then 8 month!
customer_reviews.text: Bought them as a gift for my wife 8 month ago - And now they are already broken! Suddenly the earbuds can hardly connect, range is less then 1 meter, and the sound is terrible! Can’t really recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Emil Fini Krabbenhøft

customer_reviews.title: I'm sure there's a lot better out there for the money
customer_reviews.text: Not bad but supposed to have an ambient sound setting but this is dreadful.
customer_reviews.author: Philip Wood

customer_reviews.title: Waste of money!!! With no customer support nor reply! Don’t forget long receive time(1month)
customer_reviews.text: Took a month to get the product and first day of having it, it started dropping my calls and disconnecting even though it wasn’t even 3 ft way.( back pocket) trying to return due to its connection defect. Terrible experience with no customer support or feed back from jLab will never buy another product from them. Beware this is a company that doesn’t stand by there product so if your unfortunate to get a defected one your out of luck... disguised with there way of business when it comes to situations like this . Shame on you JLabs !!!!!
customer_reviews.author: Tien Tran

customer_reviews.title: Terrible!!!!
customer_reviews.text: When they work the jlab jbud air executive are great, but they NEVER work! Worst wireless earbuds on the market, do not waste your hard earned money.
customer_reviews.author: Heather

customer_reviews.title: Left headphone connectivity issue is true
customer_reviews.text: Overall I did like the headphones. I had some people say the calls sounded clear and others say I either sounded a little far away or it sounded like I was in a tunnel. The main reason for the rating is because of the left headphone's connectivity issues. I saw other people said the same thing but I figured I'd give them a try. Well, they were right. The left side has connectivity issues and it bugs me enough for me to consider them unusable and return them. Such a shame, because it they just worked right, I would've kept then and been more than happy with them.
customer_reviews.author: TA

customer_reviews.title: Jlab Air Executive
customer_reviews.text: Sound quality is pretty good. Style and design is cool. Touch sensor on both ear pieces with different settings. So far so good. I'm happy with the purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Rodrigo Rodriguez

customer_reviews.title: Best earbuds for phone calls
customer_reviews.text: This has got to be the best earbud for voice calling. I work in very high pitch noisy area. This is the best earbud or headphones for noisy coffee shop too. The sound of the earbuds are really good. It has good bass if you like that but not overwhelming. Great all around sound for everyone. The price for these are very good and the quality is awesome. It is not multipoint so you can't connect to different devices simultaneously. It still can connect several devices one at time.
customer_reviews.author: Mark Delapenha

customer_reviews.title: Pretty solid
customer_reviews.text: At $50 I'm mostly happy with purchase. This is the only pair of ear buds that I can't get to fit my ear without really messing with it. I have a dog that used to love to eat earbuds so i've been through at least 15 pairs in the last 2 years. Battery life seems okay so far, i'm not impressed with the quality of the ambient noise passthrough but everything else sounds great. I do wish that i didn't have to manually toggle it on after the buds power down and wish the eq was more customizable but again, $50 for the battery life, quality of sound, and looks of these I'm totes fine
customer_reviews.author: Ron Sy

customer_reviews.title: Poor customer service. Low max volume.
customer_reviews.text: Max volume is way too low. Sound quality might be great but can't hear it well enough to tell for sure. Left ear bud cut out often even with the phone 1 foot in front of my face. I returned these obviously defective earbuds having to pay my own shipping. I lost $12 in shipping. Buyer beware. I have other wirefree earbuds and bought these for the battery life, which is as advertised.
customer_reviews.author: Aaron Leach

customer_reviews.title: Great out the box, but quality immediately starts failing.
customer_reviews.text: Out of the box these were amazing. Sound quality and levels were extremely impressive. However it's been 3 months and already I've lost at least 25% of the volume levels. Also connectivity can be hit or miss, which doesn't make a huge difference when listening to music (mostly volume consistency, some in and out) but effectively makes the headphones useless for phonecalls as it results in the microphone cutting out. The only thing that I'm still impressed with is the battery life. At least I haven't noticed if the quality dropping yet. In the search for an affordable set of wireless pods that will last, these don't add up.
customer_reviews.author: BMG

customer_reviews.title: Maybe not as good as the 5 star reviews
customer_reviews.text: Bass was almost nonexistent even in the bass eq mode with to much treble. When I tried with Netflix the volume was to low and the right bud keep going out of sync. I purchased these based off the great reviews, to bad the reviews were inaccurate. Returning them.
customer_reviews.author: john a oconnor

customer_reviews.title: Earbuds worked great! Until they stopped working...
customer_reviews.text: I would have given these earbuds a 4 or 5 star review as they worked great, sound was fantastic including deep bass and how seamlessly i could switch from audio to answering phone calls and FINALLY my voice didn't sound like I was under water. Also, using the blue earbud accessories helped the fit tremendously, very comfortable. I purchased these in April but in late July, I'm not sure what went wrong, my right earbud will not work no matter that i've charged to 100% and followed set up instructions. Awaiting assistance from JLABS support team...will update soon, i hope!
customer_reviews.author: N. Tal

customer_reviews.title: Stopped working after 3 months, bummer.
customer_reviews.text: So these headphones were working perfectly. Good Battery life, great sound and great for conference calls while in traffic. Unfortunately, they stopped working a little over 3 months. I went ahead and asked for a refund and they kindly offered 80% of the value even after the 3 month period. The bad thing is I am not currently in the U.S. and sending them back will cost me $70, so I have to accept I lost my money. I will be looking for another brand and hopefully don't end up. I am really disappointed.
customer_reviews.author: Guillermo from Guatemala

customer_reviews.title: Bust.
customer_reviews.text: Bought these for my girlfriend for her birthday and they were horrible! I’ve used the JLab True Wireless earbuds personally and I was pleased for the price. With these Executives, however, you would’ve thought they were a pair of $15 headphones. The nicest thing about them was the case and touch-sensors on the buds. It’s very possible that they were a faulty pair but I was altogether disappointed so I returned them and purchased some Sony’s instead.
customer_reviews.author: Pj

customer_reviews.title: Great sound
customer_reviews.text: I gave these a 4 because the mic for the calls isn’t great. People on the other line would hear a lot of background noise. I did like the 3 built in equalizer settings. The extra bass was my favorite, although that setting also reduces midrange sound. As a result you lose some volume. They went plenty loud for me though. As with all the earbuds I’ve used, I needed to use my own ear tips because the supplied are too small. They are comfortable and I could wear them for extended periods.
customer_reviews.author: Jamie M

customer_reviews.title: Great product for price
customer_reviews.text: I bought a pair over 6 months ago and work amazing still. Bought a 2nd pair for my young brother who had his for 5 months and he uses them religiously and they still look brand new. Sleek design and box. Long charge hold n quick charge in case. I was someone who bought headphones 2x week but not no more. Must have for 70$ .
customer_reviews.author: Ryno

customer_reviews.title: It’s cheaply priced for a reason
customer_reviews.text: They aren’t the loudest headphones and they certainly don’t cancel noise. I’ve tried every earhole attachment size and they still manage to fall out in the gym - I do not have weird sized ear holes like my wife, which are oddly small. After 3 months the earbud started to heat up so much I was concerned that it would combust in my ear. Yes, explode in my ear. It was preceded by some strange crackling sound for a day, and then white hot heat. I guess when you want to get a cheaper option than AirPods you have to risk burning your eardrums. Never again.
customer_reviews.author: heather

customer_reviews.title: Works Great in the beginning... then they quit
customer_reviews.text: *updating my review. These have officially quit working for me. For the last couple of months they have been cutting in and out and draining of battery quicker and quicker. Now I can barely listen for more than 30 minutes without issues. It’s a major bummer. Initial review: Love these! They fit perfectly and have different size options for the ear pads. They definitely cancel all noise in the room and the sound quality is great! The charge lasts a full day of work (about 8 hrs) and I’m a huge fan of them!
customer_reviews.author: AddyK

customer_reviews.title: TRASH HEADPHONES! - DONT WASTE YOUR TIME OR MONEY
customer_reviews.text: I read all of the reviews before purchasing these. The connection to these head phones from a cell phone or a computer is ABSOLUTELY HORRIBLE. I watched support videos and read forums online. The headphones keep cutting out, losing connection, and are overall JUST TERRIBLE. SERIOUSLY DO NOT BUY THESE - THEY ARE NOT WORTH YOUR TIME, ENERGY, OR MONEY. I will not be buying J Lab headphones EVER AGAIN!
customer_reviews.author: Tech Savvy Chicago

customer_reviews.title: LOVE THEM
customer_reviews.text: After purchasing and using these for a day i can honestly say i am very satisfied mind you jlab is generally my go to for casual listening but having used these the case charges the buds at a great speed and while not as compact as competitors is very pleasing to the eye my only gripe is the case is a little bulky so not really a pocket case but overall probably one of my favorite airpod substitutes (side note i do not own a single apple product and while the airpods are at the forefront of true wireless experience i do not want to pay 120+ dollars with comparable product being cheaper)
customer_reviews.author: richard innis

customer_reviews.title: Disappointed
customer_reviews.text: They pair very easily and quickly, but the left earbud keeps going out. People said they could hear me prior to the left earbud messing up but after 1 day they keep syncing off and on and the sound goes out. They are also much heavier than anticipated and keep falling out of my ears. I am returning them. If the left earbud wasn't an issue, I would have rated them much higher. When they are working the sound is great.
customer_reviews.author: AB

customer_reviews.title: Great sound quality but chunky, hard to fit in ear
customer_reviews.text: The sound quality appears great but it is so chunky it doesn’t fit in ear very well so will prob return
customer_reviews.author: Lori Keathley

customer_reviews.title: Not perfect by any means.
customer_reviews.text: The seller didn't show shipping info on the package as detailed in my account. Because of this it took almost 2 weeks longer to receive the order. Sound quality matters the most for me and it's really good. Connectivity could be better - more often than you want they loose connection between right and left earphone. In terms of size they are bigger than they look on images and won't fit smaller ears. And what's also important the call quality on the other end is quite bad. Most of the times people I call ask me to switch back to phone microphone. Seems like more cons than pros to them. But in my opinion sound quality beats the bad.
customer_reviews.author: Stanislav Hromov

customer_reviews.title: Great quality combined with great value
customer_reviews.text: These are a great option for anyone who wants quality bluetooth earbuds that also have microphone pass-thru. Nice sound, good battery life, and actually comfortable. The closest competing earbuds cost triple the price! (Galaxy buds, Air pods)
customer_reviews.author: Charles M Jorgenson

customer_reviews.title: WON'T STAY IN
customer_reviews.text: NO MATTER WHAT I DO OR HOW I ADJUST THEM, THEY WONT STAY IN MY EAR LIKE THEY SHOULD. I PUT THEM IN AND THEY FALL RIGHT BACK OUT 10 MINUTES LATER. PLUS THEY HURT LIKE HELL
customer_reviews.author: Dan

customer_reviews.title: Fizzled excitement
customer_reviews.text: I liked that the fit could change. The blue foam were my favorite. Size was good. Battery case was good I think it could have been engineered to be smaller though. I was getting shocked by static’s while wearing them. I felt like I should have been able to use one at a time. They can’t be”. I returned them after they just stopped working. Good concept needs work.
customer_reviews.author: Studio McCutch and MSPExcite

customer_reviews.title: They are ok.
customer_reviews.text: Knocked a star off. There are these bands that wrap around the headphone to keep in place (? Idk) but they fall off when not in use which is super annoying. Also from time to time my headphones get super echoey when I’m near my phone which I don’t understand. I have to put them back in the carrying case to “reset them” and then they go back to a normal sound. These are ok.
customer_reviews.author: Grace

customer_reviews.title: Falls out of ears..fittings hurt ears after a while.
customer_reviews.text: Falls out of ears easily. Especially when sweating or wet, even with multiple ear piece sizes. Hard to adjust in ear without pressing pause or skipping track, not much to hold on to. Other than that the noise canceling is good, the listen awareness feature is cool, good battery life. I dont think its worth the price though.
customer_reviews.author: Zack

customer_reviews.title: Sound pretty good, but have a lot of setbacks.
customer_reviews.text: * Battery life was good * Design is great * Case is nice, although a bit bulky * The active awareness feature lacks, everything sounds tinny and artificial. No concept of depth and basically useless. * Call quality is mediocre, but really has issues at times. Extremely choppy voice, picks up way too much background noise.
customer_reviews.author: Rastacola

customer_reviews.title: One more volume level, but still VERY LOUD!
customer_reviews.text: I love these earbuds so much. The fit is snug on my not so large ears but not small. Air executives have a very nice noise cancellation seal. And are great for working out. I would wish it would get just one more notch louder. Spotify premium has an equalizer just use that!! I’m in love with them! No complaints they get every job done and for a great price.
customer_reviews.author: Matthew Moran

customer_reviews.title: Left earpiece didn't work
customer_reviews.text: Looked great, but the left earpiece didn't work. They were also hard to pair with the phone. Returned.
customer_reviews.author: Richard S

customer_reviews.title: Everything has room for Improvement.
customer_reviews.text: I bought these thinking they were cool, obviously for the price they weren't going to be perfect but, they have some issues. When using these the mic seems to be always on, when I listen to music and drop something the noise will echo into the earpiece, which is absurdly annoying. It also seems one has a piece of hardware loose inside of it because when I tap the touchpad, It'll sound like a spring ringing in my ear. Sounds okay overall, there is no noise cancellation, and battery life is ok. I slightly regret purchasing these, just due to the malfunctions this pair has.
customer_reviews.author: Josie Colgrove

customer_reviews.title: Good for listening. Not good for calls.
customer_reviews.text: The good: They are good for the gym or walking outside while listening to music. The bad: Whenever i would make calls the person on the other line always kept telling me that they couldn't understand what i was saying. This is terrible because my job is to speak with people over the phone. i wanted to use it for work and now i have to look for something else and these buds weren't cheap. Fail. I'm disappointed.
customer_reviews.author: Edgar B. Olmos

customer_reviews.title: Worth ~$5
customer_reviews.text: Took me 2 weekends and a lot of online searching to even pair them for the first time. Comfort is bad, I spend a good minute each time I put them in, trying to get something that feels comfortable. Sound is poor, like you're hearing something from another room but with the bass removed. Mic is unusable, on my first call the other person asked me to switch mics as I was too quiet for them to hear. I was really looking forward to these, but they just aren't good at anything...
customer_reviews.author: Regan

customer_reviews.title: Tin can sound, uncomfortable
customer_reviews.text: I was hoping for a "good enough" option to AirPods Pro. This was so not the case. From trouble pairing them, to the weird robot sound when talking on the phone, this was unusable to me. The super hard plastic hurt my ears. Unforturnately, I had to return them....
customer_reviews.author: Christopher Kwalik

customer_reviews.title: Awesome for the money
customer_reviews.text: It all depends on how they fit your ear. The sounds is great and theres very little discomfort for me when using them for workouts. Other reviews talk about connectivity issues. I haven't found that with the Jlab exec. Worth the money!
customer_reviews.author: Dexter

customer_reviews.title: Do Not Buy These!!
customer_reviews.text: Absolutely the worst. Don't buy these. There is no noise cancelation. The sound is okay at best but when you turn them up to the fullest it seems as if your on medium but that's as far as it will go. They are huge in your ear. Often times they hurt. So again so not buy these. I repeat Do Not Buy these. They are not worth the price.
customer_reviews.author: Candace

customer_reviews.title: Great value
customer_reviews.text: Work great and a great value for the money. Function buttons are a little hard to get used to (as they are on each ear bud) but manageable. In order to switch pairing between devices it appears that one must first remove the ear buds from the current device and add to the next device (e.g. switching from PC to phone and vice versa. Do also notice a switching between ear pieces almost giving the package an odd stereo effect.
customer_reviews.author: William Hooker

customer_reviews.title: Great earbuds at a great price
customer_reviews.text: I’ve had them for a few days now and must say overall I’ve had a great experience so far. They have great sound quality The call quality is crystal clear The overall build of them is sturdy. The ear piece does make my ears a little sore but not as much as the air pods did. Only issue I’ve had so far is that the awareness mode catches and amplified sharp noises but are horrible at catching people talking to you.
customer_reviews.author: Danny_g951

customer_reviews.title: Very short battery life, low volume, choppy sound,rude customer server
customer_reviews.text: Very short battery life! barely 4 hrs! Max volume is way too low. sound quality is mediocre, very little bass. too much complaint from other end of phone call. a week after the lift earpiece gets choppy ! I returned these obviously defective earbuds having to pay my own shipping. I lost $12 in shipping. Buyer beware the Jlab customer server is very rude!
customer_reviews.author: zanezhen

customer_reviews.title: Lousy Customer Service
customer_reviews.text: Started out just fine, but about 2 months in they began to act funny, after 6 months, would not stay connected no matter what I did, they said they would replace and required that I destroy the ones I have, did that and took a picture of what I have, they sent me the same email as the 3 previous emails, it’s been weeks now and still no ear buds. I’m pretty sure I won’t see them, the promised warranty is no good! Very small customer service window and days to get a return call. Won’t buy again... very disappointed!
customer_reviews.author: Scott Shepston

customer_reviews.title: Not for active persons
customer_reviews.text: The overall quality is good, however they can’t stay in my ears once I am active. I have tried all the sizes that came in the package if it is not too small it is too big and the default size that came on the device fits best, but does not stay if I am active.
customer_reviews.author: Rasta got Soul

customer_reviews.title: Sound is out of this world. Making calls not good. There is like an echo.
customer_reviews.text: The sound of this buds are out of this world! the best ever. Disappointed with the quality of the calls. People complain they hear and echo and the sound quality is not good on their side.
customer_reviews.author: DanTheMan

customer_reviews.title: Good, could be better.
customer_reviews.text: Love a lot of things about these, but don't enjoy a couple either. They work reliable, they hold a good charge, and they connect every time. Replacement tops are a bear to find, and some aftermarket ones need to be cut down so the earbuds will seat in the charger. Also, you can't control all the functions with just one earbud in. Would also like the option to use left only, there same way you can pair the right only.
customer_reviews.author: David Settle

customer_reviews.title: So-so earbuds
customer_reviews.text: Battery can’t make it through a work day. Pairing is a bit spotty. Comfortable in the ears overall. The first set I got, one earbud stopped working after a day. The second set seem to be holding up.
customer_reviews.author: Stephanie Zeman

customer_reviews.title: JLabs needs to go back to the drawing board
customer_reviews.text: Extremely poor product, and I am hard pressed find anything redeeming. Poor connectivity - I often have to reset 2-3x to get it to pair with my car, phone or computer Poor audio - even after finally getting it to pair, the music will skip and earbuds fade out without any apparent pattern Poor call quality - while reception is usually fine (unlike with music, I have never experienced skipping), more often than not the other party complains that they have trouble hearing me when I talk through the earbuds.
customer_reviews.author: E.R.

customer_reviews.title: great sound qaulity and takes calls great
customer_reviews.text: Listening to music has great sound and balance. Taking phone calls is easy and sounds good on both ends no complaints there. You can use the right side by its self to listen to music or make calls. That would be the only complaint I would have is the right side is not my strong side for only using one. Other than that these are amazing and the blue foam ear pieces are amazing at blocking sounds and keeping them in place your ear. I wear these at my construction job and they stay in place all day.
customer_reviews.author: Mike Johnston

customer_reviews.title: Broke after about 6 months
customer_reviews.text: Worked ok for about 6 and a half months. Sound quality was decent. Mic volume was ok for true wireless earbuds. Had to speak sort of loudly to be heard. Charging case was small and convenient. A little finicky when you put the buds inside whether it would charge sometimes. Not perfect but I could live with it. After about 6 months of use, earbuds started losing bluetooth connection on any sort of obstruction (e.g. me putting the phone in my pocket or me turning my head away from the phone or computer). Sad
customer_reviews.author: HWK

customer_reviews.title: Be aware is no good.
customer_reviews.text: The “be aware” Audi feature is virtually useless because it cannot be used while music is playing and the audio is quality from the microphone sounds super tin can. Battery is ok and the value decent.
customer_reviews.author: Mr. Miguel O’brien

customer_reviews.title: Buy them
customer_reviews.text: Good set of headphones. Had Bose over ear noise canceling. They are better sounding but bulky and they do get hot. These are perfect for at my desk at work. The around awareness feature is nice to hear folks talk while u still having audio going on. For the money they are the real deal. Would receive buying the foam tips to go with as they fit better than the rubber tips
customer_reviews.author: Corey Johnson

customer_reviews.title: Finicky Recharging
customer_reviews.text: They sound fine. But are extremely difficult to recharge. The recharge case seems to only want to recharge one of them at a time. If you put one in - it will recharge. If you add another - the first stops recharging and the second begins. Sometimes after leaving them in the case for a few minutes - whichever one was recharging will stop - requiring you to go back and re-insert the ear buds every few minutes during the entire charging process. I would avoid these and find another set of earbuds.
customer_reviews.author: B Alex Tyler

customer_reviews.title: Not worth the price
customer_reviews.text: These headphones were a disappointment. They were not comfortable and kept falling out of my ears. There is no on/off power button so it's either charging or losing charge at every moment. Their most positive attribute seems to be the sound quality which was good.
customer_reviews.author: Shira

customer_reviews.title: Just not working for me.
customer_reviews.text: I just cant't get these to work for me. Volume very low, forget about wearing just one. No matter what I do I can't get the volume up. I was hoping that these would work. Maybe I just got a bad pair.
customer_reviews.author: Bill C

customer_reviews.title: Above and beyond
customer_reviews.text: Damn good sound quality and the battery life is great especially the charging dock that it comes with to charge them on the go plus they give you a link on YouTube on how to properly burn your ear buds so they can reach their full potential with proper lows mid’ s and highs something I never knew about
customer_reviews.author: juan razo jr

customer_reviews.title: Air pods competitor!
customer_reviews.text: Been having problems with the Bluetooth, and having to set my headphones back on the charging case, to establish connection again. Other than that, great ear buds! Sometimes they fall off, but mostly stick during sweaty hours.
customer_reviews.author: Javier Sanchez

customer_reviews.title: Great sound, bad pairing
customer_reviews.text: I loved these! The sound quality is good and I love the ability to cancel the noise or have awareness. However, the earbuds did not want to stay paired to my phone or each other.
customer_reviews.author: Tisa Lira

customer_reviews.title: Good True Wireless Earbuds
customer_reviews.text: Their not the most comfortable for long times, but the sound quality is very good. Definitely worth the purchase
customer_reviews.author: Brody Bogoski

customer_reviews.title: BOOOOOOOO :(
customer_reviews.text: These headphones don't fit my ears well at all. They have very odd comands and sometimes if you just tap them they pause or skip your song. They have fallen out of my ears numerous times and I would just spend the extra money to buy apple airpods next time.
customer_reviews.author: kat

customer_reviews.title: What a bargain!!!
customer_reviews.text: For 70 bucks, vs iPhones version, my brother works at Apple as an engineer and he couldn't tell the difference when I called him the other day,, sound quality is a 9!! solid 9, cant be happier.
customer_reviews.author: kc135rpilot

customer_reviews.title: The earpiece  should be  able to  fit in my ear.
customer_reviews.text: My daughter brought a pair from wallmart ,and she love them, and I brought my pair off of amzon, first of all, the headphones came with no instructions, and they have changeable earpiece, but they keep sliding out of my ear, it's not worth the money ,I spent.
customer_reviews.author: Sheila.Thomas

customer_reviews.title: Fist pair I buy, don't really know what's  most important.
customer_reviews.text: I've just had them a couple of weeks. Nice the way they fit, great sound! Getting used to the features. Good quality, great price.
customer_reviews.author: Ricardo J. Diaz

customer_reviews.title: Perfect in every sense
customer_reviews.text: This earbuds works execellently. It sits well on the ear, the sound quality is great and the controls are very simple. the battery life looks forever. What is more, it has noise cancellation that actually works.
customer_reviews.author: Emmanuel Baba-Lola

customer_reviews.title: Good headphones but audio stutters
customer_reviews.text: Good sound quality and comfortable fit but the audio stutters a lot randomly on Android (OnePlus 5) and sometimes the connection will drop. When it stutters, the sound changes so that the right earbud starts playing louder and this can only be fixed by triggering Google Assistant. If the audio stuttered less this would be an amazing purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Darren Y.

customer_reviews.title: sounds good, but terrible for meetings, pairing is ify
customer_reviews.text: what you hear is good, but during meetings people can't hear you well, it cuts out a lot. connection gets lost some times battery life is good material quality is good I regret buying it
customer_reviews.author: Leandro

customer_reviews.title: Decent for music. Terrible for phone calls.
customer_reviews.text: Pick up entirely too much background noise on phone call. Callers on the other end complain about how loud background noises are and it drowns out my voice.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Don't buy these
customer_reviews.text: Sound quality is terrible. Left earbud cuts off the whole time. The only good thing is they stay in your ear. I sent them back.
customer_reviews.author: M Rivera

customer_reviews.title: Good. Dont Buy
customer_reviews.text: They were good for the first 3 days, then one started acting up, first by the touch controls not working on the right earbud, i somehow got it to start working again by manhandling the touch pad. But then about 2 days later, the same earbud just stopped giving out sound. Everything else works perfectly. Also there id a pretty noticeable amount if latency. I expected a lot more if JLab since these were the only headphones I used before I got beats.
customer_reviews.author: shanda bailey

customer_reviews.title: Audio presets made the greatest difference.  Sound quality excellent
customer_reviews.text: I had previously purchased a similar item, different style same brand and gave them not a great review BUT this earbuds really are top of the line on my list and for a reasonable price - Yes, will recommend!
customer_reviews.author: LH

customer_reviews.title: Great ears bud

customer_reviews.title: Great True Wireless earphones without high price tag..
customer_reviews.text: The sound is excellent whether I'm listening to Jazz, folk, or even Drum & Bass. (Yes, I have eclectic taste in music) I've taken a few calls with these and the sound was crystal clear on both ends. The only thing Is that you cannot wear them for more than a couple of hours before they start to make your ears hurt.
customer_reviews.author: J. Murch

customer_reviews.title: Function controls stopped working

Was really enjoying the battery life until the right command ear bud has no function controls, if it shuts off due to inactivity, I have to set into charging case and then remove to get it to reconnect. I have had these 2 weeks maybe.... and the memory foam tips are pointless!
customer_reviews.author: c.j.

customer_reviews.title: they do the job, best for walking but only short while
customer_reviews.text: they are ok for the price. but just ok nothing really mind blowing, they are not really comfortable unless you use foam tips they get dirt easily. battery life is good, mine came with box open, i bought them new at release

customer_reviews.title: Left ear cutting out intermittently

After going down to about 90% battery the left ear will begin to cut out intermittently. It's extremely distracting and frankly unusable.
customer_reviews.author: RACKGNOME

customer_reviews.title: Sensitive
customer_reviews.text: Crappy I can't even turn my head w/o them acting up...I think they are either messed up ...also noticed that they are acting like hearing aid everything is louder I dropped something and it was loud as hell do something is off with these I would love to buy a new pair bc they are cool I think these are just a messed up pair.
customer_reviews.author: Crystal

customer_reviews.title: Worked great at first
customer_reviews.text: They worked great for the first couple of weeks. Now they won't turn off when you try to power them off. The say they are connected but you don't hear any music. Not happy with this product at all.
customer_reviews.author: Chris Voelker

customer_reviews.title: Best pair of BT earbuds I have used!
customer_reviews.text: This is my second pair of these ear buds. the first set worked great, I even washed them in the laundry and they still worked, then I lost one so i bought a new pair. The foam ear tips are so much more comfortable then the usual rubber kind. battery life is great, sound quality is great and the be aware mode is nice for when you need to hear your surroundings.
customer_reviews.author: Jon H.

customer_reviews.title: Nice sound quality but too big !
customer_reviews.text: Sound great. I dont like the fit. Too big for my ears to fit in snuggly. I switched the tips to smallest size and still too big. Feel like they are going to fall out and loose them. Not for small ear canal! :(
customer_reviews.author: kathy o

customer_reviews.title: Don’t work after 2 months
customer_reviews.text: These started out and ok and did what they advertised. However, 2 months in and the syncing operation began to fail. First it failed between the two headphones and then I started to get syncing issues to my actual phone. These things are junk. Don’t buy these, just spend the extra $30 and get a reputable brand.

customer_reviews.title: Not something we enjoyed
customer_reviews.text: Did not like the setup process. And the synch process. We are returning them.

customer_reviews.title: Great Earbuds
customer_reviews.text: Bought these as a gift for our son- he says excellent feel, loved they came pre-charged and ready to use, surprisingly good microphone and says sound quality rates real well. Nifty case, big enough not to lose or misplace too.
customer_reviews.author: Thomas M. Schultz

customer_reviews.title: Excellent product
customer_reviews.text: Excellent voice with nice bass, comfortable to wear , the operating range away from the phone is around 8 meters which is excellent .. nice design .. the charging case with built in cable is brilliant and made of really solid and elegant material .. fully recommend

customer_reviews.title: Second pair broke just like the first

customer_reviews.title: Touch sensor problems

customer_reviews.title: Love it!

customer_reviews.title: Beyond disappointed

customer_reviews.title: Great Sound and Battery Life
customer_reviews.text: Sound and charging along with Bluetooth connection are great. I have had one small issue with fit and still working on swapping the additional earbuds back and forth to find the best option. Not meant for exercising or high impact activities but great for all other uses - phone and listening.
customer_reviews.author: Lisa

customer_reviews.title: Great deal, some improvements though.
customer_reviews.text: The sound wasn’t awesome. It could be richer with a few more EQ settings. I love case and battery battery life And the aware feature. The auto pairing. A wireless charging case would be nice too. Very comparable to AirPods except the sound.
customer_reviews.author: Ryan W. Todt

customer_reviews.title: Horrible sound and not loud at all
customer_reviews.text: For anybody looking for a good sounding pair of ear buds stay away from these! I'm very unhappy with the volume of these and even with a selected EQ level nothing helps. I will be returning these for a refund.

customer_reviews.title: Won’t charge!!
customer_reviews.text: Sound quality isn’t bad, but wish i could listen long enough to enjoy it. Right bud will not hold a charge. Turns on, says low battery, then turns off all within 2 minutes. Very unhappy.

customer_reviews.title: Don’t buy!!
customer_reviews.text: These ear phones are great.. except the volume sucks I can barely hear anything music sounds like it is on the lowest setting and I can barely hear someone talking to me on the phone constantly asking them to repeat themselves because I can’t hear them.. don’t buy these unless you want to have problems hearing music and people
customer_reviews.author: Austin Ferguson

customer_reviews.title: Too Bulky
customer_reviews.text: They’re very big so if you have dumbo ears these are for you. Even with the little ear buds, these are just too bulky for me. Sound quality is 7/10 for calling/answering Music . Battery life 7.8/10 Good quality for the price. I’d say the main issue with these are the comfortability, I’m used to Apple ear buds.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Way better value than Airpods.
customer_reviews.text: My second pair. Lost one last week on a run. Love them. Most bang for the buck.
customer_reviews.author: Greg1971

customer_reviews.title: Great sounding earbuds, but not comfortable
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these earbuds, and within 2 days had to return it. My ears started paining if i put these on even for as less as 15 minutes. Size was slightly bigger than i expected, but they felt quite sturdy and very less chances of them to fall off under heavy regimes.
customer_reviews.author: AbbasAli Abdeali Gulabiwala

customer_reviews.title: A great buy overall

customer_reviews.title: Compact with good sound.
customer_reviews.text: Nice sound, punchy bass. Get loud enough. Touch controls work well.

product_meta.title: JLab Audio JBuds Air Executive True Wireless Bluetooth Earbuds + Charging Case - Black - C3 Calling with Dual Microphones - Long Travel Playtime - Bluetooth 5.0 Connection - 3 EQ Sound Settings
product_meta.description:
GO Lead.

The JBuds Air Executive keep you GOing for travel and business, with 30+ hours of playtime and dual microphones providing a crystal-clear listening experience for both phone calls and music. From the office to the airport, a 6-hour battery life in each earbud and 24+ extra hours in the case provide all day listening. An ergonomic design plus included Cloud Foam eartips keep the earbuds comfortable for long days and an IP55 sweat resistance offer the durability you need wherever you go. You can even adjust your sound with our C3 Sound technology, allowing you to choose between three EQ settings; Signature, Balanced, and Bass Boost.

Long Travel Playtime

The earbuds hold a 6-hour battery life and the compact case provides 24+ additional hours of playtime. The JBuds Air Executive automatically start charging when placed in the case, which recharges with the integrated patent-pending USB cable.

C3 Calling

The JBuds Air Executive feature stereo audio and C3 (crystal clear clarity) phone calls from upgraded dual microphones. One mic picks up and eliminates surrounding noise while the other picks up your voice for clear conversations anywhere, anytime.

Auto On & Connect

The earbuds will automatically turn on and connect to each other right out of the case, as well as instant connect to your phone. Utilizing Bluetooth 5, this is our fastest hands-free connection yet.

Control It All

Featuring touch sensors to control all your music and phone calls with just a tap or hold, it’s easy on-the-GO. Turn on or off Be Aware Audio to let ambient noise in for safe listening or zone out to just your music.

Cloud Foam Comfort

Enjoy endless comfort while traveling with the included Cloud Foam Eartips that mold perfectly in place. Trust the JBuds Air Executive’s durability with an IP55 water and dust resistance.
